-- 
Merkel, Sarkozy Reach Position on Greek Debt

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-07-20T23:00:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/merkel-sarkozy-find-common-position-on-greece-debt-crisis-after-talks.html
German Chancellor  Angela Merkel  and
French President Nicolas Sarkozy reached a “joint position on
Greece’s debt situation” after seven hours of talks at the
Chancellery in Berlin today, Steffen Seibert, Merkel’s
spokesman, said in an e-mailed statement.  The two leaders “listened to” arguments brought forward
by  Jean-Claude Trichet , president of the European Central Bank,
who attended part of the meeting, Seibert said. They exchanged
views with European Union President Herman Van Rompuy by
telephone, Seibert said.  The joint Franco-German position will be presented to
leaders at today’s summit in Brussels by Van Rompuy, Seibert
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rainer Buergin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net  